 <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/febreeza?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /rude EZboard</span><hr size=1> To be honest I don't know any females that would beg for stuff either.  I am sure there are some out there, but I don't know them.  Most of the females I know, including myself, would send them tells, telling them get off their butts and work for it like the rest of us.<br>
<br>
I dislike begging and do not give to beggers.  I have helped people numerous times who had legitimate reasons for asking for help.  ie. The ogre in Kelethin who couldn't buy bandages cause he couldn't fit through the door.  I ran up to the orc lift and he had been sending /ooc's asking for someone to help him for 5 minutes.  He had the money and items to sell he just couldn't fit through the door of the inn.  I helped him.  As well as the gnome asking for food and water.  Gave him 5 of each.<br>
<br>
But the person who runs up to me and says; &quot;I'm a newbie can you give me some money?&quot;  The answer is simply no.  I have also had newbies come up and ask me for the armor off my body.  I usually ignore them and leave.  Once gave a newbie leather armor that I had just earned enough to replace with chain.  He went and sold it, cause he said he wanted to save up enough to buy a big sword for 200pp.  Later when he yelled for help cause he was dying to a low level mob.  I went over and watched, then left.  *shaking head* <p><b><i><h5>Febreeza Tinytank</i></b><br>
<b><i>Level 44 Warrioress - Ayonae Ro</i></b><BR>
<b><i>Level 11 Warrioress - Sol Ro</i></b><BR>
<BR>
<b><i>Mischievous Nonnsense</i></b><BR>
<b><i>Level 22 Rogue - Ayonae Ro</h5></i></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/14/01 8:40:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /rude EZboard</span><hr size=1> That's a good point.  If people are polite in asking for help, I'll usually buff them and send them out to fight.  In the chance I'm actually in a city and I get a tell from a begger, I'll sometimes use the opportunity to role-play.<br>
<br>
Begger: &quot;Can you help me?  I need some money to buy spells/equipment/whatever.&quot;<br>
Jzonn: &quot;I recommend you proceed to the city gates and assist in the clean-up effort there.&quot;<br>
Begger: &quot;What do you mean?&quot;<br>
Jzonn: &quot;I understand there are a good many vermin and other undesireables hanging about.  Exterminating them and selling anything savagable would be a good way to earn the cash you seek.&quot; <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/14/01 8:49:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/febreeza?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /rude EZboard</span><hr size=1> Oooo Jzonn I like that.  I will keep that in mind for future use.  <br>
<br>
I once asked someone who sent me a tell asking me for pp where they got my name.  They said that they saw me running into the city, and since I had such nice armor (HAH I'm a crafted blueberry) they knew that I just had to have lots of money.  Informed him that when people have really nice armor like this it usually means they are broke cause they spent all their money on their really nice armor.  And NO I don't have any money to give you.  Then put him on /ignore. <p><b><i><h5>Febreeza Tinytank</i></b><br>
